reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 8, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfectly sized and adjustable along the length of the seat back.
reviews.reviewText: My office chair at work is 12 years old and perfect for me. But due to COVID-19 restrictions, I can't be there and am trying to make due with my home office chair, which is comfortable, for an hour or two, but not well suited for all day support. Things were getting sore, really sore, by the end of each day. Limited shopping for a new chair revealed that most are still way too big for me, and more money than I want to spend for what I hope is a temporary situation (four months in). This mesh back support has an elastic strap that slides over the back of the chair and is adjustable up/down for wherever you need it. It's not too bulky and gives a little under the weight of my back when I lean into it. It doesn't make my back sweat. And I can work without getting sore. That's the best part.

reviews.reviewTitle: Support in chairs for short legs
reviews.reviewText: I have short legs and slouch while sitting because I do not reach the back of chairs and have no support in my lumber area. I padded the inside of the curve, put a towel over it and added it to the back of my sofa chair. The massage area gives firmness and support that fits the lumber area perfectly. It’s firm enough to put a heating pad on it to get direct heat. The mesh can be used to hold it in unique places with a bungee cord. Less pain and fidgeting. Luv it. Bought another for my vehicle.
It fitted perfectly on my chair but a bit uncomfortable on my couch
